    "comment": "Rationale: deletion of SNAP-25 leads to strongly reduced neuron survival, and, in the few surviving cells, impaired arborization, reduced spontaneous release, and complete arrest of evoked release.. Experimental description: Results; \"To study the different functionality of SNAP-25 variants, we used Snap-25 null **mice** (Washbourne et al., 2002).\"\n\nAlthough SNAP25 is overexpressed, this is only to show that the effect of SNAP25 KO on SV release is really caused by loss of SNAP25.; the species of OE SNAP25 is irrelevant to the species determination therefore.",
